The paper deals with optimizing spectral efficiency for wireless networks and cognitive radios, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI) sub-categories. The consideration of both SISO and MIMO links suggests that the paper may also fall under the multiple-input multiple-output (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also deals with minimizing interference, which is a key concern in cognitive radio networks (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between longer transmit duration and wider bandwidth versus higher transmit power, which suggests that it may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
